snippet.textDisplay:
Love this song really inspiring lost my older brother back in December he died under police custody and before he passed I moved in back with moms and finally reconnect with her after 3 years of being homeless and being a alcoholic I had the time to apologise to her for all the bullshit I put her threw now I'm living with my younger sisters who are living on there own I'm also trying my best to reconnect with them and doing my best to become a older brother that they desperately need since we lost our oldest brother.
My younger sisters are helping me out with scholarships and financial aid so I could go back college and are also helping me with a job.
My family has been threw allot in these past 3 months and my brothers passing is finally taking a toll on us finally realizing he's never coming back.
This song is really motivating me to become the older brother again and to fight in court against these corrupt cops and against a corrupt system.
Thank you so much #JellyRoll I've been listening to your music since I was in middle school now I'm 24 yrs old and slowly getting my life on track .
This song couldn't of had came out at the right moment.
Good timing on releasing the video looking forward to getting your new album.
Much love from the Southwest
Diné/Navajo Tribe
#NativePride
